==Anglo-Saxon==

===Verb===
'''ǽwnian'''

# to marry, wed

===Pronunciation===
*ae:w·ni·an, ye·ae:w·ni·an; 

Note: this verb may appear with or without the [[ge-]] prefix, without a change in meaning

===Declension===
*Class 2 Weak Transitive Verb
====Present Tense====
=====Indicative=====
*Singular: ic ǽwnie, þu ǽwnast, hé ǽwnaþ
*plural: wé, gé, híe ǽwniaþ
=====Subjunctive=====
*Singular: ǽwnie
*plural: ǽwnien
=====Imperative=====
*Singular: ǽwna!
*plural: ǽwniaþ!
=====Participle=====
*ǽwniende
====Past Tense====
=====Indicative=====
*Singular: ic ǽwnode, þu ǽwnodest, hé ǽwnode
*plural: wé, gé, híe ǽwnodon
=====Subjunctive=====
*Singular: ǽwnode
*plural: ǽwnoden
=====Participle=====
*geǽwnod
====Inflected Infinitive====
*tó ǽwnienne

===Etymology===
*Derived from [[ǽ]] {{f}}, ''matrimony, marriage''.

